Police in Kipkelion have arrested a teacher for allegedly defiling a Form Four student.  Area police commander Peter Omondi said the 25-year-old suspect was arrested for allegedly defiling a 17-year-old girl.  Mr Omondi said police rescued the teacher from the angry public who wanted to lynch him at his rental house.  The suspect allegedly lured the girl into his house on Wednesday night.  Noordin Haji alleges plot to kick him out of office as row with DCI soars  Granny, 98, attacked and raped  Two police officers face probe for assault  Businessman stabbed to death while closing his shop "In the morning, the residents spotted the girl at the teacher's house and raised alarm, attracting an angry mob who wanted to lynch the suspect. Police officers acted swiftly and rescued the suspect."  The suspect is being detained at Fort-ternan Police Station.  The officers took the girl to Fort-ternan Sub-county hospital for medical examination.  The suspect will be arraigned to face defilement charges once police complete investigations.  ntanui@standardmedia.co.ke     ICC GHOSTS BACK: Wanted lawyer surrenders to ICC, Paul Gicheru accused of interference  Ndugu wawili wadaiwa kumuua kaka yao baada ya mzozo wa hela  Cyber Crime In Kenya:Global Malware currently on the rise as economy loses Billions to digital vice By Peter Ochieng  | 34 minutes ago By Julius Chepkwony | 12 hours ago By Kennedy Gachuhi and James Munyeki | 12 hours ago By Nikko Tanui | 12 hours ago